title: [Nanetta's Cafe, Pastry Kitchen ]
description: Wide wooden countertops, freshly scrubbed after a long day's baking, await the bustle of work that will accompany sunrise.  An open cookbook has fallen to the floor.  A large window with an extra wide sill fills the back wall.  Fragrant evening breezes occasionally send yellow checkered curtains grazing the tops of pies left overnight to cool.  A punched tin pie cupboard set near the open doorway is stocked with desserts favored by locals and visitors alike.

Cluttered wooden countertops are dusted with flour and several rounded balls of dough rest upon each, ready to be rolled into the pastry chef's next sumptuous creation.
